  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>To determine miR200 levels (fold change) in blood samples.</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline (one time).</time_frame>
    <description>MicroRNAs (miRs) are noncoding small RNAs, which regulate numerous physiological and pathological processes. miR200 levels will be measured in blood samples collected from control subjects, non-IPF ILD and IPF patients. These samples will be used for identifying biomarkers for IPF.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
